^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 291 - April 8, 2002^*N
^*BBy Fred Gitelman^*N }
^-
This week's deal is a defensive problem that I faced at the recent San Diego Regional. I was playing with ^*BSheri Winestock^*N in a knockout team match when this week's deal was played.

Sheri and I are pleased to announce that the World Headquarters of ^*BBridge Base Inc.^*N will be moving from Toronto to Las Vegas some time in May. It may take us a little while to settle into our new home, update all of our web pages, etc. We apologize in advance if our service is slower or less reliable than usual during this transition period.

A lot of people have been asking us, "Why are you leaving Canada to live in the United States?" and "Why Las Vegas?". Bridge is a big part of the reason why we are moving to America. My regular partner, ^*BBrad Moss^*N, is an American and we would like to try to play together in future World Championships. That means we have to be living in the same country. Also, moving our business to the United States will be good for a number of reasons (lower taxes for example). Las Vegas is particularly appealing due to good real estate values, lots of friends living there, no state income tax, and good weather.

The concept of leaving Canada is strange for Sheri and me. We have both lived in Toronto all of our lives and both of our families live here. Most of my best bridge moments have come when I was playing for Canada (including my recent Gold Medal at the IOC Grand Prix in Salt Lake City). Sheri has also represented Canada in the World Championships. We will always be proud to say that we were born in Canada, but we will also be proud to call America our home.
